From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: winex11: can_activate_window allows top-level WS_CHILD

Mirror of the win32u WS_CHILD fix (0037): a top-level WS_CHILD editor
(parent==desktop) must be activatable, else WM_TAKE_FOCUS never reaches
set_focus and wine's foreground stays NULL. The win_data_mutex lock-ordering
fixes that the old 0039 also carried now live in patch 0020; the wmtf focus
diagnostic has been dropped. This patch carries ONLY the can_activate_window
relaxation.

diff --git a/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c b/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
index 5c135c89894..0ac1cd0226c 100644
--- a/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
+++ b/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
@@ -589,7 +589,19 @@ static inline BOOL can_activate_window( HWND hwnd )
     }
 
     if (!(style & WS_VISIBLE)) return FALSE;
-    if ((style & (WS_POPUP|WS_CHILD)) == WS_CHILD) return FALSE;
+    if ((style & (WS_POPUP|WS_CHILD)) == WS_CHILD)
+    {
+        /* vstpoc patch 0039 (winex11 mirror of 0037/013-focus-ws-child-top-level):
+         * allow a TOP-LEVEL WS_CHILD window (VST plugin editor — vst_host
+         * effEditOpen passes the desktop as parent HWND, the plugin then makes
+         * its editor WS_CHILD) to be activatable. Upstream returns FALSE for ALL
+         * WS_CHILD here, so WM_TAKE_FOCUS never reaches set_focus, wine's
+         * foreground stays NULL, INPUT_KEYBOARD is dropped, and typed characters
+         * never reach the editor. A real child (parent is another window) is
+         * still refused. */
+        HWND parent = NtUserGetAncestor( hwnd, GA_PARENT );
+        if (parent && parent != NtUserGetDesktopWindow()) return FALSE;
+    }
     if (style & WS_MINIMIZE) return FALSE;
     if (NtUserGetWindowLongW( hwnd, GWL_EXSTYLE ) & WS_EX_NOACTIVATE) return FALSE;
     if (hwnd == NtUserGetDesktopWindow()) return FALSE;
